<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/589.</note>
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-23"><hi rend="smallcaps">July</hi> 23,
                                1911</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The minister is informed by the Haitian Government that it has been
                            decided to blockade Fort Liberté, Gonaives, and St. Marc. He has replied
                            that the blockade must be effective to be respected.</p>
                    </div>
